ned oil interests to create petróleos mexicanos pemex el aguila formally dissolved itself on may   eagle oil and shipping companyedit main article eagle oil and shipping company pearson started to acquire steam tankers to carry the oil that he hoped to produce armstrong whitworth on the river tyne launched ss san cristobal  tons in  and swan hunter also on tyneside launched ss san antonio  tons in  pearson also bought ss james brand  tons which had been built by armstrong whitworth in  and renamed her san bernardo in  pearson founded the eagle oil transport company in the uk to take over his ships and carry mexican eagles products and the anglomexican petroleum company in the uk to sell mexican eagles products outside mexico eagle oil transport immediately ordered  modern steam tankers at a cost of £ million eagle oil transport lost a number of ships to enemy action in the first world war after the first world war eagle oil transport renewed and expanded its fleet it bought numerous new tankers including six of about  tons each when royal dutch shell bought pearsons oil interests that included eagle oil transport and anglosaxon petroleum as well as mexical eagle petroleum in about  the eagle oil transport company was renamed the eagle oil and shipping company in about  the company started adding a new generation of motor tankers of about  tons each eagle oil and shipping was registered in the united kingdom therefore after  although the mexican government had nationalised mexican eagle petroleum eagle oil and shipping remained a subsidiary of royal dutch shell after  the fleet continued to carry oil from the gulf of mexico to the uk during the second world war the company played an important role in supplying petroleum and petroleum products to the united kingdom oil tankers were a particular target in germanys economic warfare against the uk enemy action sank  eagle oils ships and killed at least  officers men and dems gunners serving aboard them mv san demetrio reached the clyde in  with a cargo of aviation spirit despite having been damaged by shellfire from the admiral scheer among the ships lost was mv san demetrio  tons which was famous for surviving a naval bombardment by the german heavy cruiser admiral scheer in  that set the tanker on fire san demetrio was repaired and returned to service but the uboat u torpedoed and sank her in the western atlantic off virginia in  with the loss of  lives in  the ministry of war transport placed a number of empire ships under eagle oil and shippings management one was sunk by enemy action in  but after the war the company bought two of the surviving ships from the ministry the company also bought two t tankers that had been built in the usa the company further renewed its fleet with  new ships between  and  and maximum tonnages steadily rose towards the end of the decade the royal dutch shell parent group absorbed eagle oil and shipping in  notesedit  godley  pp    a b c d godley  p   a b godley  p   godley  p   a b godley  p   a b godley  p   godley  p   a b c d godley  p   godley  p   watkins thayer the petroleum industry of mexico san josé state university   a b c godley  p   a b godley  p   godley  p   godley  p   godley  p   a b c d e f godley  p   a b godley  p    oil deal royal dutch and shell companies buy mexican eagle stock new york times  though the reference says shell oil company now the name of royal dutch shells us subsidiary it also says the price was split  royal dutch shell the exact split of the  royal dutch – shell transport joint venture and their  merger thus the  buyer must have been shell transport not shell oil company  kennedy paul p  big oil company closes its books el aguila of mexico holders vote to dissolve new york times   marconi transatlantic wireless telegraph  form  line cowdray interests to build fleet to carry mexican oil products new york times   godley  pp    lloyds register of shipping london lloyds of london   accessdate requires url help  t